POLICE are looking for an escaped prisoner who was awaiting trial.Henry Onoh escaped from the Kgosi Mampuru Correctional Services in Tshwane on Saturday morning. He was due to be sentenced at the Pretoria Magistrates Court on Monday.He was arrested for a number of crimes, including rape, house breaking and theft.Police suspect he might have fled to another province.He has been linked to other serious crimes in Mpumalanga and KwaZulu-Natal.Gauteng police spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Lungelo Dlamini said Henry had been in custody since last year.The escaped prisoner is considered armed and dangerous.&ldquo;Police are investigating the circumstances which led to his escape.&ldquo;Any information that could lead to the arrest of the prisoner might be rewarded,&rdquo; he said.Police are appealing to anyone with information to contact CrimeStop at 08600 10111.Alternatively, those with information can contact Detective Warrant Officer Louis Hoffman on 083 650 0820.